00:09:41.789 --> 00:09:46.815
So, it's all a balance of dark
energy versus dark matter,

00:09:46.815 --> 00:09:50.494
or matter, in general,
but the dark matter

00:09:50.494 --> 00:09:53.337
predominates.
And, at the moment,

00:09:53.337 --> 00:09:57.220
it is true that the dark energy
is--there's more of it.

00:09:57.220 --> 00:10:00.239
It exerts more,
more of an influence on the

00:10:00.239 --> 00:10:03.021
Universe;
therefore, the Universe is not

00:10:03.021 --> 00:10:05.610
just expanding,
but also accelerating.

00:10:05.610 --> 00:10:08.893
We know that because these
points are above the line,

00:10:08.893 --> 00:10:12.396
not below the line.
But this didn't always have to

00:10:12.396 --> 00:10:17.050
be true.
This balance changes with time.

00:10:20.340 --> 00:10:25.375
So, currently,
DE blows away the DM,

00:10:25.375 --> 00:10:29.580
but this can change.
This changes.

00:10:29.580 --> 00:10:36.649
In fact, this is almost certain
to change with time.

00:10:36.649 --> 00:10:40.193
And the reason is that the
energy density of the dark

00:10:40.193 --> 00:10:43.872
energy and the matter density of
the dark matter behave

00:10:43.872 --> 00:10:47.620
differently as you change the
size of the Universe.

00:10:47.620 --> 00:10:56.499
It's all about the density
here, so, matter density in the

00:10:56.499 --> 00:11:01.295
past.
You have the same amount of

00:11:01.295 --> 00:11:06.510
matter, but the Universe was
smaller.

00:11:10.860 --> 00:11:15.039
Density is equal to mass over
volume.

00:11:15.039 --> 00:11:18.889
So, if you have the same
M, but smaller V,

00:11:18.889 --> 00:11:22.390
this would have to have been
bigger in the past.

00:11:26.159 --> 00:11:28.764
And, in fact,
it goes as the scale factor

00:11:28.764 --> 00:11:31.500
cubed, or 1 over the scale
factor cubed.

00:11:31.500 --> 00:11:35.899
Just because volume goes as a
linear scale cubed.

00:11:35.899 --> 00:11:38.981
So, in the past,
there was--the matter density

00:11:38.981 --> 00:11:41.720
was much greater than it is
right now,

00:11:41.720 --> 00:11:44.594
and therefore,
the gravitational force trying

00:11:44.594 --> 00:11:48.317
to hold the Universe together
was greater than it is right

00:11:48.317 --> 00:11:52.783
now.
But the Cosmological Constant

00:11:52.783 --> 00:12:01.760
is constant, and what that means
is that its density is constant.

00:12:05.830 --> 00:12:11.238
And what that means is that,
in the past,

00:12:11.238 --> 00:12:18.270
the dark energy density was the
same as it is now.

00:12:24.289 --> 00:12:27.394
That's just the way this
particular piece of Einstein's

00:12:27.394 --> 00:12:29.649
equations works.
It's a constant.

00:12:29.649 --> 00:12:31.714
Now, if you're about to ask the
question, well,

00:12:31.714 --> 00:12:34.361
how does anything behave that
way, I'm going to give you the

00:12:34.361 --> 00:12:36.480
same answer.
